				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just bought a <a href=http://www.microsoft.com/hardware/mouseandkeyboard/productdetails.aspx?pid=005>Microsoft Wireless Optical Mouse</a>  to replace my <a href=http://www.microsoft.com/hardware/mouseandkeyboard/productdetails.aspx?pid=008>Microsoft Wheel Mouse Optical</a>.
<br />

<br />
I'm curious what you guys think about Optical Mice in general. Did I make the right choice going Wireless? Are trackballs in again? Hell is Logitech better than Microsoft? (To date, I've never met a piece of Microsoft <span style="font-style: italic">hardware</span> that I didn't like. Software? Thats another story).
<br />

<br />
What about fancy features on mice in general? Obviously the scroll wheel is a standard feature now, but what about extra buttons? (Microsoft InteliMouse have a whole bunch of buttons besides Left, Right, Wheel)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Mage) - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=816142" target="_blank" class="postlink">Venerable Eiyana Lunaire</a> (Cleric) -  <<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enshadowed</a>>
