			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally? LogiTech TrackMan Marble - preferably the older pale-plastic 3-button one, but the modern dark plastic 2-button 1scrollwheel works too (the new ones are a bit harder to clean than the old, but oh well).
<br />

<br />
I'm not good at tolerating mouse lag - I have a KVM switch for 4 of my computer, and while they share moniter&keyboard they each have individual mice, as the switch's mouse lag (though minor) was intolerably uncomfortable/annoying.  I'd imagine I'd have similar issues with a wireless mouse, although since I use a trackball I have far less motivation to try wireless anyhow.
<br />

<br />
I prefer trackball over mouse primarily because you have to do so much less - your hand is basically stationary other than finger movement, and is largely or fully supported by the case.  Assuming you find a trackball with a good fit to your hand, it winds up taking very little energy to use and is much "easier" (and, I assume, healthier) on your hand.
<br />

<br />
I admit, it did take me about 2 years to become comfortable with using a trackball, but now I'd never go back.  Sooo much easier on my wrist & hand muscles, and just easier to use imo.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
