			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the corded mouse generally agreed upon by most twitch gamers to be the best is the Logitech Mx500, for Wireless the Mx700.  I own the Mx500 and love it myself.  Personally, I'd never buy a wireless mouse.  I just don't need it, and corded will always be more reliable.  There was a mouse a long time ago called the "Razor Boomslang" which was specifically designed for playing shooters and was supposed to be awesome, but the manufacturer was bought out and I'm not sure if the products are still being made.
<br />

<br />
As for microsoft mice, I've owned my share of them in the past, and I don't have any quarrels with them.  All have been decent.  I can tell you for sure that trackballs are definately NOT in hehe... but wireless is certainly becoming more popular, and I think they are equal to corded mice now for the most part.  Basiclly it just comes down to whatever feels good in your hands.  Oh...and one piece of advice, I wouldn't install any mouse driver ever (even ones from Microsoft) unless it just will not work with default drivers.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370607" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tiiden Vandorgriffin</a>
<br />
65 Magician, Rodcet Nife</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
