				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ive got the same mouse, got it a few months ago and the only thing id suggest is make sure you buy some very long lasting rechargables, at first i was using some crappy 1400NiMH ones but they didnt last all that long, had 3 sets lying around and a superb fast charger so wasnt a problem, but without a decent charger, its a pain in the butt.
<br />

<br />
Im in the UK so dont know how helpfull this will be, but these guys do the best batteries ive ever used <a href="http://www.digibattery.co.uk/astro/index.htm" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.digibattery.co.uk/astro/index.htm</a>, there high speed charger does anything in an hour, and i can go a couple of months most of the time before needing to recharge <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
But aye, the mouse, cant fault it, not had a single prob with it even with fast paced FPS games (the first optical mice had big probs here), the extra buttons ive got setup to open my spell book at different pages and its a really comfortable mouse to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
