			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Trackballs are too unwieldy to move the cursor a large amount, unless you set the sensitivity really high and then they're too unwieldy to move the cursor a small amount.
<br />

<br />
Optical mice beat regular mice for the simple facts that you never have to clean them and they last several orders of magnitude longer.
<br />

<br />
I've used a cordless keyboard and cordless optical mouse with EQ for the last year or so.  Haven't had a single problem, and actually, haven't had to replace the batteries yet either.  I'm using the Microsoft combo package that comes with both k/b and mouse (both wireless).
<br />

<br />
I also have never met a piece of Microsoft hardware I didn't like.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
