			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I guarentee I have the strangest mouse setup of anyone.
<br />

<br />
A few years ago I started to get carpel tunnel in my right hand from all the constant mouse use on the computer.  The pain was bad and faced with surgery I set out to teach myself to use my left hand instead.  The best mouse I found for this was a Logitech Marble trackball which could be used for either hand.  After a few months of frustration I finally mastered the technique and I swear I am better with my left hand and this little trackball then I ever was with my right in nearly every game and application including EQ.
<br />

<br />
The exception was 1st and 3rd person shooters (Quake, Unreal, Jedi Outcast & Academy) which I could never master left handed with my little optical trackball.  For that I use the MS Wireless Intellimouse Explorer (also optical) with my right hand.  The pain in my right is gone nowadays as long as I don't overdo it. 
<br />

<br />
Now here is the strange part.  Since the trackball is connected via a PS2 connection and the MS mouse connects via USB I can keep both mice connected and working at the same time.  Thus I actually have two working mice connected to my computer at all times, one for each hand.  It's strange but I love it.  Both mice are excellent and I use them interchangeably.<br />_________________<br />Orthien 65 Mage - Torvonnilous
<br />
--------------------------------------------------
<br />
Time you enjoy wasting is not time wasted.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
