				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Trackballs sadly have dropped significantly in markeshare over the past few years. The few that are out there aren't terribly impressive. I still swear by the corded Logitech TrackMan Marble (palm-shaped, three-buttons/wheel, thumb ball) for non-drawing use.
<br />

<br />
Logitech continues to make the best corded and non-corded mice and keyboards. They are probably a year or two ahead of Microsoft in developing and bringing to market more reliable and better performing technologies.
<br />

<br />
(Right now I use a tiny little optical mouse that came from my travels in Japan. Its just comfortable for me in the way it fits my hand and I don't do a lot of "on-the-fly" mousing at all in EQ.)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
