				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I also want to chime in and say I love my wireless optical Logitech MX700!  I've never had a problem with jerkiness or any odd occurances with this mouse, and I use it for shooters as well as everything else.  Would definately recommend it.  You also can't beat the fact that the transceiver is also a recharging station, so no batteries to buy every other month!
<br />

<br />
Logitech also just came out with a corded "gaming" mouse based on their MX optical engine, but with faster throughput than their standard MX engine.  I forget the model number, but I saw it in Best Buy the other day.  It's a cool metallic red color, and looks just like the MX700 (only corded).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
