			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">MX700 here, and I won't go back to MS's version of optical (Explorer 3 or 4, can't remember)... they have an issue in EQ that made me switch...
<br />

<br />
The drivers would uninstall or get removed while playing. Don't know why this happened, and it also effected my keyboard, which was a standard Natural Keyboard. Most times when this happened, I would have to do a hard shutdown.
<br />

<br />
I tried various drivers, reinstalling the os and drivers, etc. This was a mouse issue, but I believe that it was related to the USB version of this, as I don't recall having the problem if I used the ps/2 converter
<br />

<br />
Also, if you used a KVM like I did, and several other people I know did, don't be holding onto one of the left or right buttons when you switch between systems (this could only be used ps/2 style). What would happen was that both systems would lock up... the one you just left and the one you just toggled over to.
<br />

<br />
I have not used the MX700 with the kvm to see if the issue, but none the less, accuracy, lack of system driver disassociation, and a wireless mouse that I can recharge every few days win my vote.
<br />

<br />
Yeah Logitech!!</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by hopalong on Thu Apr 01, 2004 10:46 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
