			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use an explorer 3.0 Microsoft optical mouse. My first one after about a year developed a problem (was a known issue as it was prior to the 3.0 release). I called Microsoft and a new one arrived in the mail in a few days free of charge. So service was very good. As for issues, none at all. Mine is a corded mouse, and as the cord is out of the way, I have no issues with it at all. Would a wireless work, sure, but for me at least it isn't needed. I would never go back to a regular ball mouse again, just too many issues with them.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
